HEADWORD: Chelidonic
<hw>Chel`i*don"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Celandine</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or
derived from, the celandine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chelidonic acid</b></col>, <cd>a weak acid extracted from
the celandine (<spn>Chelidonium majus</spn>), as a white crystalline
substance.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chelidonium</ent>⟦br⟧
